CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F419A1737406297
OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Simeon
OL,4,CMayou
OL,6,F"We all got down there and thought
OL,7,Fthis would be it. After a while the
OL,8,Fofficers and captain came down and the
OL,9,Fcaptain took his hat off, put it under
OL,10,Fhis arm, looked round and said: 'Well
OL,11,Flads I expect every man to stand by
OL,12,Fhis duties. Splice the mainbrace, we
OL,13,Fare going to invade Normandy.'"
OL,15,FDuring and after the crossing,
OL,16,Fhundreds of Allied planes were
OL,17,Foverhead.
OL,19,FThe next order given to Fusilier was
OL,20,Fto bombard enemy positions and protect
OL,21,Fthe landing force.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/5
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
